    "summary": "With more than 25 years of international experience in various types of industry Marius Hoogendam is an experienced senior manager. Marius has broad experience in the private sector and also has six years of experience with major government projects in real estate and PPP in renewable energy.\nHe works well in a multinational environment with different cultures and where he can make use of his language skills. He communicates well from the level of mechanics on the shop floor to the level of the supervisory board. He thinks on a strategic level, likes to get things done and is result driven. He is a team player and works well with entrepreneurial CEO\u2019s as sparring partner. To complement his knowledge he recently studied financial law, which he considers essential as corporate governance has become more and more important.\nAs European controller has gained experience with different types of generally accepted accounting principles among other US GAAP, UK GAAP, Dutch GAAP and IFRS.\nMarius was trained as an auditor by Arthur Andersen & Co. The first six years of his career he worked as an auditor and in corporate finance for the big 6 from offices in the Netherlands and Hungary. He worked in multinational teams on audits, privatizations and valuations in various types of industries.",
